This paper deals with the task of contextualizing knowledge graph facts, which involves generating additional and useful facts related to a given fact. This task involves natural language processing, machine learning, and knowledge representation, which are all sub-fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves information retrieval (cs.IR) as it deals with augmenting search results with additional facts. The use of neural networks and supervised learning to rank models also falls under the sub-field of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves natural language processing techniques such as entity tagging and distant supervision, which are part of computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper deals with knowledge graphs, which are a type of database, falling under the sub-field of databases (cs.DB).
